84
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:06,639
Always say thank you and you're welcome when you're talking to other people.

85
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:07,379
That's right.

86
00:04:07,419 --> 00:04:09,400
And that's one way of being polite.

87
00:04:10,099 --> 00:04:17,139
Now also when we are describing the way that you speak to someone or the way that you write, you can be very direct.

88
00:04:17,579 --> 00:04:21,500
Now being direct means that you say exactly what you want or exactly what you're thinking.

89
00:04:22,459 --> 00:04:26,879
So maybe if we're talking to this company, you say, hi, I want this.

90
00:04:27,019 --> 00:04:27,980
I will pay this much.

91
00:04:28,279 --> 00:04:28,600
Thank you.

92
00:04:28,819 --> 00:04:28,939
Bye.

93
00:04:28,939 --> 00:04:29,300
Right.

94
00:04:29,860 --> 00:04:31,279
That's maybe too direct.

95
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:36,319
So sometimes you need to be a little less direct and say nice things in an email.

96
00:04:36,740 --> 00:04:37,000
That's right.

97
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:44,759
So maybe you want to say to someone that you don't really like the clothes they're wearing, You say, hey, do you like my new shirt?

98
00:04:44,839 --> 00:04:47,819
And if you're very direct, you would say, no, I think it's very ugly.

99
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:48,860
I hate it.

100
00:04:49,079 --> 00:04:49,379
Right.

101
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,259
That's too direct.

102
00:04:50,339 --> 00:04:55,180
So maybe you would say, I don't really think it suits you very well.

103
00:04:55,339 --> 00:04:57,920
Or I think a different color would be better on you.

104
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:58,459
That's right.

105
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:00,540
So that's being a little bit less direct.

106
00:05:01,459 --> 00:05:06,240
Now obviously, if you're too direct with someone, you may offend that person.

107
00:05:07,019 --> 00:05:07,279
All right.

108
00:05:07,379 --> 00:05:14,720
To offend is a verb and to offend someone means to say something that makes them unhappy or upset or even angry.

109
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:21,540
So going back to the same example of the shirt, if you say, I think that shirt is very ugly, that person might be offended.

110
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:22,800
Gosh.

111
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:31,759
Or maybe if you say, you know, I think people with brown hair are so ugly and there's someone next to me with brown hair, they say, oh, I'm offended.

112
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:32,279
Right.

113
00:05:32,439 --> 00:05:34,339
I'm not ugly, but I have brown hair.

114
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:35,019
That's right.

115
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:35,779
Okay.

116
00:05:35,779 --> 00:05:42,399
So you don't want to offend anyone by being too direct or you don't want to have anyone feel offended.

117
00:05:42,980 --> 00:05:49,620
