00:12:12,879 --> 00:12:13,220
All right.

257
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,720
So this is a way to end a letter.

258
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:24,659
You can say sincerely or best, but it's a very nice way to end if you just say all the best and then you say, you know, after that you have a comma and then you sign your name.

259
00:12:24,879 --> 00:12:25,379
That's right.

260
00:12:25,899 --> 00:12:26,259
All right.

261
00:12:26,259 --> 00:12:29,759
Let's listen to our dialogue one last time and we'll be back to talk a little bit more.

262
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:38,679
Melanie, can you help me with something?

263
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:45,840
We need to finalize the account with the Mexican Embassy, and I need some advice on phrasing this letter correctly in English.

264
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,039
Sure, Tracy.

265
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,340
Let me just get my laptop.

266
00:12:57,059 --> 00:12:57,539
Right.

267
00:12:57,799 --> 00:12:58,100
All set.

268
00:12:59,879 --> 00:13:02,899
OK, so to whom it may concern.

269
00:13:02,899 --> 00:13:04,039
I am writing.

270
00:13:04,679 --> 00:13:07,639
Um, Tracy, I think that's a little too formal.

271
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:11,659
I know you want to be polite, but you've already made contact with them.

272
00:13:11,659 --> 00:13:15,139
So in English, you can be a bit more relaxed in the opening.

273
00:13:15,659 --> 00:13:16,639
OK, more relaxed.

274
00:13:17,139 --> 00:13:17,600
Got it.

275
00:13:18,259 --> 00:13:19,600
Hey, Sally, what's up?

276
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:20,700
It's Tracy here.

277
00:13:21,159 --> 00:13:22,759
Just OK, Tracy.

278
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,059
Now it's too relaxed.

279
00:13:25,539 --> 00:13:27,360
You've still got to show some respect.

280
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:29,600
How about starting with Dear Miss Cooper?

281
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,240
I'm writing to confirm.

282
00:13:32,039 --> 00:13:32,240
Great.

283
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:32,539
OK.

284
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:49,480
Dear Miss Cooper, I'm writing to confirm the final quotation for the full page back cover color advertisements you requested for the spring issue of Viola magazine.

285
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,279
That's great.

286
00:13:51,279 --> 00:14:02,159
The final costing, including advert design and production, comes to $45,600 RMB.

287
00:14:03,039 --> 00:14:09,980
We want payment 10 working days before publication, or we will cancel the ad.

288
00:14:10,799 --> 00:14:11,539
Thanks for...

289
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:12,139
Whoa.

290
00:14:12,580 --> 00:14:14,200
OK, back up a second, Tracy.

291
00:14:14,779 --> 00:14:16,220
That's too direct.

292
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:22,960
But can I suggest you say, please note that the final payment is due two working weeks before publication?

293
00:14:23,639 --> 00:14:24,940
You don't want to offend her.

294
00:14:25,860 --> 00:14:26,860
OK, you're right.

295
00:14:27,419 --> 00:14:30,200
Then I can just end with all the best, Tracy.

296
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:35,279
Maybe I'd play it safe and just finish with yours sincerely.

297
00:14:35,799 --> 00:14:37,139
That's more professional.

298
00:14:38,059 --> 00:14:39,600
Oh, Melanie, you're a lifesaver.

299
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:40,480
Thank you.

300
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:59,159
So talking about ending formal emails or emails that you're writing to clients, colleagues, we can say sincerely and your name, sincerely, Marco, you can say all the best, best regards.

301
00:14:59,799 --> 00:15:12,379
Now, I've noticed that some people who aren't native English speakers, sometimes they will close a letter, maybe even a formal letter, saying yours truly, Marco, for example.

302
00:15:12,379 --> 00:15:15,580
Is that really appropriate for a business setting or a client?

303
00:15:15,580 --> 00:15:17,399
I would not use yours truly.

304
00:15:17,759 --> 00:15:26,480
Maybe if you're trying to build a relationship with your client and you're very honest, but it seems to me to be very personal.

305
00:15:26,860 --> 00:15:27,419
Very romantic.

306
00:15:27,759 --> 00:15:28,539
Yes, yours truly.

307
00:15:29,820 --> 00:15:39,139
So I would say in that case, use sincerely or kind regards or regards, which are a little bit more professional and less emotional.

308
00:15:39,519 --> 00:15:47,139
If you want to have a romantic letter, you can say, you know, all my love or love or yours truly or yours faithfully.

309
00:15:47,940 --> 00:15:57,200
This is a very important topic, I think, because many times in school we do learn how to write letters, but usually they are more personal letters.

310
00:15:57,440 --> 00:16:04,779
And so we memorize that usually at the end of the email or the end of the letter, you say yours, Marco, or yours truly, Marco.

311
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:09,480
And although it is correct, it's not really appropriate for a professional setting.

312
00:16:09,919 --> 00:16:10,279
That's right.

313
00:16:10,279 --> 00:16:20,879
So just as a reminder, if you're signing off your email or your letter and you're at an office here in your company, you want to say best or best regards or some of the things that we talked about here today.

314
00:16:21,259 --> 00:16:21,480
Very good.

